Add cold, salted @water{300%ml}(cold and salted) to a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting
lid. Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and @chicken stock{1%sachet} and bring to the
boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Remove the #pot{} from the heat. Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready
to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the
@chilli{1}(halved lengthways, deseeded and thinly sliced). Halve the
@bell pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded, sliced into strips). Peel and grate
the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated).

Add @flour{1%tbsp} to a large #bowl{}. Season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}. Add the @Irish chicken breast{260%g}(diced) and toss to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}(a drizzle). When hot,
fry the chicken until golden all over, shifting as it cooks, ~{7-8%minutes}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to
> packaging used to keep it fresh.

Add the onion and bell pepper. Fry until starting to soften, stirring occasionally,
~{4-5%minutes}. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper. Add the garlic and cook until
fragrant, ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @red Thai style paste{1%sachet}, @ketjap manis{2%sachets}, @water{25%ml} and
chilli (use less if you don't like spice). Cover and simmer until the chicken is
cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Remove from the heat and stir in the @peas{120%g}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel the sauce needs loosening.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}. Taste and season with salt and pepper, if required.
Divide the rice between #bowls{} or #plates{}. Top with the glazed chicken and veg.
Finish with a drizzle of @sweet chilli sauce{1%sachet}.